    "text": "AI &amp; Data Transformation  \nCase Study: Large British Building Society  \nStrategic Partnership for AI Enablement,  \nModern Data Platform Migration &amp; Data Governance  \nConfidential  \nExecutive Summary  \nConfidential  \nAI &amp; Data Transformation – Case Study  \nThis case study documents a comprehensive AI and Data transformation programme spanning three strategic pillars:  \nAI Centre of Excellence  \n- Established GenAI CoE\n- Experimented with 4+ use cases\n- ~90% time savings on complaints letters\n- Graduated use cases to production  \nModern Data Platform  \n- Azure + Databricks + dbt\n- MS SQL &amp; Teradata migration\n- Customer data mastering\n- &gt;30% faster code development via GenAI  \nData Governance  \n- 205 CDEs traced end-to-end\n- 400+ DQ rules operationalised\n- 78 systems mapped\n- Reconciliation controls defined  \nThe programme has delivered measurable business impact across all three pillars, reducing costs, improving compliance, and building a scalable foundation for AI-driven innovation.  \n1. AI Centre of Excellence  \nSetup, Experimentation &amp; Production Use Cases  \nConfidential  \nAI &amp; Data Transformation – Case Study  \nAI CoE – Problem Context  \nConfidential  \nAI &amp; Data Transformation – Case Study  \nThe organisation recognised the transformative potential of Generative AI but lacked a centralised structure to experiment responsibly, govern AI deployments, and scale proven use cases into production.  \nWithout a coordinated approach, there was a risk of fragmented AI initiatives, inconsistent quality standards, and inability to demonstrate measurable business value from AI investments.  \nCoE Foundations (Q4 2023)  \nLeadership  \n- Clear accountability\n- Delivery governance  \nTeam  \n- Cross-functional\n- Shaped &amp; mobilised  \nProcesses  \n- Standardised delivery\n- Central collaboration  \nGovernance  \n- Operational model\n- Responsible AI  \nAI CoE – Use Cases Delivered  \nConfidential  \nAI &amp; Data Transformation – Case Study  \nUse Case 1: Complaints Letter Writing (CRAiG)  \n- 1,300 bespoke letters/week, 40 mins each manually\n- GenAI drafts letter, human reviews in &lt;5 mins\n- REACT-based prompts outperformed few-shot\n- PII redaction, model monitoring, threat modelling\n- Piloted Feb–Sep 2024, graduated to production  \nUse Case 2: Call Transcript Analytics  \n- Sensitive data redaction via Azure Language AI\n- Automated call summarisation\n- Root cause &amp; areas-of-interest extraction\n- Nuanced sentiment beyond NLP/ML\n- Emotion detection with detailed reasoning  \nUse Case 3: QA/QC AI Assist  \n- Scaled call screening from 5% manual to 100% GenAI-enabled\n- Step-change in quality assurance coverage\n- Automated compliance checking  \nScaling the Pipeline  \n- Fraud Analysis PoC &amp; pilot\n- Contracts analysis PoC &amp; pilot\n- Figma-to-React code conversion\n- GenAI Platform Federation with API Management  \nAI CoE – Key Metrics &amp; Benefits  \nConfidential  \nAI &amp; Data Transformation – Case Study  \n~90%  \nReduction in letter  \ndrafting time  \n4 / 5  \nAvg. accuracy &amp;  \nrelevancy score  \n100%  \nCall screening  \ncoverage  \nKey Benefits  \n- Scalable AI platform with federated governance, API management and model monitoring\n- Pipeline of 10+ use cases across Customer, Colleague and IT Operations domains\n- Responsible AI practices embedded from inception: threat modelling, PII redaction, model risk evaluation\n- Integration roadmap with Lakehouse, solution accelerators, agentic workflows and small language models  \n2. Modern Data Platform Migration  \nAzure, Databricks &amp; dbt  \nConfidential  \nAI &amp; Data Transformation – Case Study  \nModern Data Platform – Problem Context  \nConfidential  \nAI &amp; Data Transformation – Case Study  \nThe organisation operated a fragmented legacy data landscape comprising MS SQL-based data warehouses, Teradata-based data marts, and mainframe-hosted Customer Information Systems (CIS). This created significant technical debt, high infrastructure costs, limited data accessibility, and constrained advanced analytics.  \nLegacy Systems in Scope  \nMS SQL / Mainframe CIS  \n- Customer Information Systems on Unisys mainframe\n- Multiple data warehouses &amp; marts\n- Manual, siloed data processes  \nTeradata Vantage  \n- Enterprise data warehouses\n- Complex stored procedures\n- High licensing costs  \nCustomer Data  \n- Fragmented across CIS, SAP and operational systems\n- Limited mastering capability\n- Inconsistent data delivery  \n2.1 MS SQL &amp; Mainframe CIS Migration  \nConfidential  \nAI &amp; Data Transformation – Case Study  \nSolution  \n- Migrated mainframe CIS to modern data lakehouse on Azure\n- Modular, reusable, version-controlled dbt models\n- Medallion architecture: Bronze/L0 and Gold/L2 layers\n- Performance-optimised ETL aligned with lakehouse principles\n- Orchestration via Azure Data Factory &amp; Control-M\n- Rigorous DQ through testing and validation in dbt\n- Standardised extracts (CSV, TXT) for business consumers  \nBenefits  \n- Decommissioning of legacy mainframe systems, significantly lowering infrastructure costs\n- Cloud-native architecture improving data accessibility &amp; agility\n- Centralised, well-governed pipelines ensuring regulatory compliance\n- Scalable foundation for real-time processing, ML &amp; AI initiatives\n- Freed budget for innovation and modernisation  \nEnding Unisys reliance – migrating customer data and FC/RC feeds to SAP  \n2.2 Teradata Data Warehouse Migration  \nConfidential  \nAI &amp; Data Transformation – Case Study  \nSolution  \n- Consolidating all data assets from Teradata Vantage to Databricks on Azure\n- Target completion: Q1 FY 2026–27 (June 2026)\n- SME-led evaluation of migration strategy &amp; architecture\n- Collaborative workshops in Pune with client stakeholders\n- GenAI-based techniques and assets using GitHub CoPilot to accelerate Teradata-to-dbt conversion\n- PoC on complex data mart codebase validating accelerated approach\n- Medallion Architecture Bronze milestone delivered ahead of schedule  \n&gt;30%  \nReduction in code  \nbuild &amp; test  \n- Fast-tracked delivery against stringent timelines\n- Validated GenAI-accelerated approach for time-to-value\n- Upfront architectural design for future readiness  \n2.3 Customer Data, Mastering &amp; Analytics  \nConfidential  \nAI &amp; Data Transformation – Case Study  \nSolution  \n- Customer data feeds migrated from legacy CIS to SAP and Azure lakehouse\n- Centralised data pipelines with built-in validation and auditing\n- End-to-end data delivery for business consumers &amp; external systems\n- Foundation for self-service BI and advanced customer analytics  \nBenefits  \n- Single, authoritative view of customer data across the organisation\n- Faster, more flexible access improving decision-making\n- Higher data accuracy and consistency for regulatory compliance\n- Enablement of advanced customer analytics, segmentation &amp; personalisation  \n3. Data Governance  \nData Lineage &amp; Reconciliation Controls  \nConfidential  \nAI &amp; Data Transformation – Case Study  \nData Governance – Problem Context  \nConfidential  \nAI &amp; Data Transformation – Case Study  \nThe legacy data estate lacked visibility into how Critical Data Elements (CDEs) flowed across 78+ systems and 6 functional areas, creating significant compliance risk and data quality gaps.  \nSpecific challenges existed in Eco Crime and Payments Screening, where the inability to trace data lineage end-to-end posed regulatory and operational risks.  \nThe organisation needed to:",
