    "text": "- Compute data lineage for CDEs – establishing baseline maturity\n- Measure data quality across in-scope functional areas\n- Review technical data reconciliation for Payments Screening\n- Promote capability building within BAU teams  \n78+  \nSystems reviewed  \n6  \nFunctional areas  \nin scope  \n150+  \nSMEs consulted  \nData Governance – Solution  \nConfidential  \nAI &amp; Data Transformation – Case Study  \nData Lineage  \n- 6 dataflow diagrams &amp; 108 interface contracts\n- 205 CDEs visualised end-to-end\n- Comprehensive mapping of areas, CDEs, interfaces &amp; SMEs\n- Augmented existing information in Planview  \nData Quality Rules  \n- Technical rules derived from lineage metadata\n- 400+ DQ rules &amp; SSDs for 205 CDEs\n- SAS tooling configured for automated checks\n- 2 DQ dimensions: Conformity &amp; Completeness  \nReconciliation Controls  \n- CDE-level: record count, field value &amp; format matching\n- Interface-level: job control, error thresholds, alerting\n- Auto-halt on mismatch with detailed logging\n- Payments Screening maturity assessment (20 SMEs)  \nCapability Transfer  \n- Active coaching of BAU colleagues\n- Sustainable capability building\n- Successful handover for ongoing operations\n- Knowledge embedded in organisational tooling  \nData Governance – Key Metrics &amp; Benefits  \nConfidential  \nAI &amp; Data Transformation – Case Study  \n205  \nCDEs traced  \nend-to-end  \n400+  \nDQ rules  \noperationalised  \n78  \nSystems mapped with  \nfull lineage  \nKey Benefits  \n- End-to-end data lineage providing full transparency for regulatory compliance\n- Proactive data quality monitoring reducing compliance risk\n- Maturity assessment enabling targeted improvements in Payments Screening\n- Comprehensive mapping augmenting organisational knowledge\n- Capability transfer ensuring sustainable governance beyond the engagement  \nSummary  \nThis programme demonstrates the value of a strategic, partnership-driven approach to AI and Data transformation:  \n- AI CoE: Responsible experimentation delivering ~90% efficiency gains, with a pipeline of 10+ use cases across Customer, Colleague &amp; IT Operations\n- Modern Data Platform: Legacy decommissioning with &gt;30% development acceleration through GenAI-based techniques and assets using GitHub CoPilot\n- Data Governance: 205 CDEs traced, 400+ DQ rules, and comprehensive reconciliation controls across 78 systems  \nConfidential  \nAI &amp; Data Transformation – Case Study",
